BACKGROUND: Despite potentially severe and fatal outcomes, recent studies of 
solid organ transplant (SOT) recipients in Europe suggest that hepatitis E virus 
(HEV) infection is underdiagnosed, with a prevalence of active infection of up 
to 4.4%.
OBJECTIVES: To determine the cost-effectiveness of introducing routine screening 
